WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:24.000
ShadowOps is shown as a collaborative experimental fork using the real laptop-safe local runtime, not a reproduced CUDA training run.

00:24.000 --> 00:50.000
Mission Control explains a synthetic GitHub supply-chain scenario, risk evidence, and a held supervisor decision.

00:50.000 --> 01:18.000
The S3 public-access scenario is repository-provided synthetic data with no cloud account or external action.

01:18.000 --> 01:52.000
The browser calls the local FastAPI decision endpoint and clearly labels the result as local with no production execution.

01:52.000 --> 02:18.000
A local-only FORK override and quarantine view demonstrate safe UI states without changing infrastructure.

02:18.000 --> 02:46.000
Benchmark values load directly from the checked-in laptop-safe report; CUDA checkpoint comparison was not reproduced here.

02:46.000 --> 03:20.900
The incident report closes the workflow. Attribution, upstream ownership, and model-evaluation gates remain explicit.
